rComments: Amazing Prof. Very patient in answering questions after lectures. Also, his explanation really makes difficult content seem easy.

Everyone seems to like his lectures, but I didn't that much. His lectures are not very interactive (i.e., he talks about the material and writes on the board without really ensuring the students understand.) I don't think he's a bad prof, he's very likeable, and I got a good mark, but I didn't feel like I gained a ton from this class. Sorry

One of the best instructors I've had in the math department. Travis knows how to present undergraduate mathematics to students who are still adjusting to proof-based math. Lectures provide numerous motivations, examples, intuitions as well as proofs.
great lecturer he knows how to teach and he knows the stuffs well highly recommended

Travis is the best prof I have even known in my life so far. He is the best young prof uoft can offer. As a super hilarious genius, he delivers enjoyable and enrich lectures. For sure he is an extremely talented mathematician, you ll feel being blessed taken his course. He has the magic of transforming incomprehensible concept into intuitive ideas

What a true gem! Loved his sense of humour, quality and very detailed lectures. Definitely makes you enjoy math even if you never did before! Be prepared for his tough tests. Just an all round great human.
Very knowledgeable. Amazing lecture. Wonderful prof.
Amazing prof. Take his course u ll not regret it.

Travis is one of the best profs at uoft. His lectures are absolutely amazing. He cares about his students. He always stays behind after lecture and even after his office hours, to ensure you understand everything. He is hilarious, so you won't get bored in his 3-hr lecture. He is also quite handsome and hot. Choose him as your prof if possible.
